### 3. American Express Gold Card - Best Perks

**Key specs:**
- Sign-up bonus: 60,000 points after $6,000 spend in 6 months
- Rewards rate: 4x on dining and groceries (up to $25K/year), 3x on flights, 1x on everything else
- Annual fee: $325
- APR: N/A (charge card, pay in full monthly)

**Why it made the list:**

4x points on groceries up to $25K/year with no category cap anxiety. The $325 annual fee is steep, but factor in the $120 dining credit ($10/month) and 4x on dining, and the effective cost drops to around $205. This only makes sense if you also eat out frequently and can use Amex transfer partners for travel. For pure grocery cashback, the Blue Cash cards win.

**Real-world scenario:** Spending $500/month on groceries (points valued at 1¢ each)

- Monthly rewards: $20.00
- Annual rewards: $240.00
- Dining credit: $120.00
- Annual fee: $325
- **Net annual value: $35.00** (only worth it if you maximize dining + travel redemption)

